      "text": "Heark-en, ye wom--en, and__ give ear un-to the voice__ of joy,__ for I have tram-pled down ty--rant Ha---des and raised the world from__ cor-rup--tion. Has-ten ye quick--ly and__ pro-claim the glad-some tid--ings to__ My friends; for I have willed__ that joy__ shine forth thence up-on all My__ cre-a--tion from whence there first came__ forth sor--row."
